<span class="headers">Learn Tailoring</span>
<p>
<a href="http://www.gucomics.com/archives/view.php?cdate=20001224"><img src="http://www.eqtraders.com/images/articles/gu_12242000.jpg" width="200" height="300" border="0" align="left" /></a>
            <p>
            <p>Tailoring is the art of working with pelts, hides, and silks in 
              order to make armor and various containers. It is one of the easier 
              skills to get started, but one of the hardest tradeskills in which 
              to grandmaster. Three races (halflings, wood elves and erudites) 
              also have tailoring as their cultural specialty.
            <ul>
              <li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g110&menustr=040110000000">How to Become a Mistress Tailor</a> 
                - by Sinuuyanea Nocturne of Quellious</li>
              <li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g111&menustr=040110000000">Myrron's Beginner's Guide to 
                Tailoring</a> (last updated March 5, 2003)</li>
              <li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g112&menustr=040110000000">A Non-Tailor's Guide 
                to Getting Tailored Velious Armors</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=62&rsa=Tailoring&sb=item&sub=other&menustr=080110000000">Tailoring Recipes</a></li>
